cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper deals with a computer vision problem of recognizing risky lane change behavior in driving videos using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a deep neural network, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The problem of recognizing risky driving behavior is also related to robotics and autonomous driving, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves the use of pre-trained models and transfer learning, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of risk estimation, which is related to cybersecurity and privacy, falling under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
